answer_en: Nothing in particular happens if you go outdoors in cold weather
question_en: What happens if you go outdoors in cold weather?
output_en: going outdoors in cold weather can lead to hypothermia, frostbite, and other cold-related health issues if not properly dressed.
backtranslated_output_en: going outdoors in cold weather can lead to hypothermia, frostbite, and other cold-related health issues if not properly dressed.
question_fr: Que se passe-t-il si vous sortez par temps froid ?
output_fr: vous pourriez attraper un rhume si vous sortez par temps froid sans protection adéquate.
backtranslated_output_fr: you could catch a cold if you go out in cold weather without proper protection.
question_de: Was passiert, wenn Sie bei kaltem Wetter nach draußen gehen?
output_de: wenn sie bei kaltem wetter nach draußen gehen, kann ihr körper versuchen, wärme zu erzeugen, indem er zittert und die blutgefäße zusammenzieht, um die wärme im körper zu halten.
backtranslated_output_de: When you go outside in cold weather, your body may try to generate heat by shivering and constricting blood vessels to keep heat in.
question_cs: Co se stane, když vyjdete ven v chladném počasí?
output_cs: vyjít ven v chladném počasí může způsobit podchlazení nebo nachlazení, zvláště pokud nejste vhodně oblečeni.
backtranslated_output_cs: going outside in cold weather can cause hypothermia or a cold, especially if you are not properly dressed.
question_is: Hvað gerist ef þú ferð utandyra í köldu veðri?
output_is: ef þú ferð utandyra í köldu veðri án réttrar fatnaðar, getur það valdið ofkælingu eða annarra heilsubresta.
backtranslated_output_is: If you go outside in cold weather without proper clothing, it can cause hypothermia or other health problems.
question_zh-CN: 如果在寒冷的天气里外出会发生什么？
output_zh-CN: 在寒冷的天气里外出可能会导致体温下降，容易感冒或体感不适。
backtranslated_output_zh-CN: Going out in cold weather may cause your body temperature to drop, making you more likely to catch a cold or feel unwell.
question_ja: 寒い日に屋外に出るとどうなるでしょうか?
output_ja: 寒い日に屋外に出ると、身体が寒さに適応しようとして血管が収縮して体温を維持しようとします。寒さにさらされると体温が下がり、寒さによるリスクが高まります。
backtranslated_output_ja: When you go outside on a cold day, your body adapts to the cold by constricting your blood vessels to keep you warm. Exposure to the cold can lower your body temperature, putting you at increased risk for cold-related illnesses.
question_ru: Что будет, если выйти на улицу в холодную погоду?
output_ru: если выйти на улицу в холодную погоду без соответствующей одежды, можно подвергнуться гипотермии.
backtranslated_output_ru: If you go outside in cold weather without proper clothing, you can become hypothermic.
question_uk: Що станеться, якщо вийти на вулицю в холодну погоду?
output_uk: якщо вийти на вулицю в холодну погоду без належного одягу, можна захворіти на грип або переохолодитися.
backtranslated_output_uk: If you go outside in cold weather without proper clothing, you can get the flu or hypothermia.
question_ha: Me zai faru idan kun fita waje a cikin sanyi?
output_ha: idan kun fita waje a cikin sanyi, zai faru kun samu sanyi.
backtranslated_output_ha: if you go out in the cold, you will catch a cold.
